The paper deals with the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for segmentation of Whole Slide Images (WSIs) of histology slides. This falls under the domain of computer vision, which is covered by the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also proposes a novel Representation-Aggregation Network (RAN) for capturing spatial context, which involves learning patch-level representation and aggregating context from a grid of neighbouring patches. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are covered by the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The paper also deals with the segmentation of tumour in WSIs of breast cancer tissue sections, which involves medical imaging, covered by the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large images, which is covered by the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
